In article <2qmdro$5ib@eff.org> Stanton McCandlish, mech@eff.org writes:
> They goofed a bit.  They force you to agree to the license agreement
they
> keep in the PGP directory, but you can't get to it to read it before you
> agree to it, because you have to agree to it to get access to the PGP
> directory.  Brilliant.  ;)

This is totally incorrect.

anon ftp to /pub/PGP and retrieve the document "license.txt"

After reading it, and assuming that you agree with the provisions, telenet
to the site and learn the access method.  You can then fetch the files.

BTW: pgp25src does include all of the documentation.
